{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:joshua.19",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "joshua",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Joshua 19 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:1",
      "text": "The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of Simeon, according to its families; and its inheritance was in the midst of the inheritance of the tribe of Judah.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:2",
      "text": "And it had for its inheritance Beer-sheba, Sheba, Moladah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:3",
      "text": "Hazar-shual, Balah, Ezem,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:4",
      "text": "Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:5",
      "text": "Ziklag, Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:6",
      "text": "Beth-lebaoth, and Sharuhen—thirteen cities with their villages;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:7",
      "text": "En-rimmon, Ether, and Ashan—four cities with their villages;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:8",
      "text": "together with all the villages round about these cities as far as Baalath-beer, Ramah of the Negeb. This was the inheritance of the tribe of Simeon according to its families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:9",
      "text": "The inheritance of the tribe of Simeon formed part of the territory of Judah; because the portion of the tribe of Judah was too large for them, the tribe of Simeon obtained an inheritance in the midst of their inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:10",
      "text": "The third lot came up for the tribe of Zebulun, according to its families. And the territory of its inheritance reached as far as Sarid;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:11",
      "text": "then its boundary goes up westward, and on to Mareal, and touches Dabbesheth, then the brook which is east of Jokne-am;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:12",
      "text": "from Sarid it goes in the other direction eastward toward the sunrise to the boundary of Chisloth-tabor; thence it goes to Daberath, then up to Japhia;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:13",
      "text": "from there it passes along on the east toward the sunrise to Gath-hepher, to Eth-kazin, and going on to Rimmon it bends toward Neah;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:14",
      "text": "then on the north the boundary turns about to Hannathon, and it ends at the valley of Iphtahel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:15",
      "text": "and Kattath, Nahalal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem—twelve cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:16",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of Zebulun, according to its families—these cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:17",
      "text": "The fourth lot came out for Issachar, for the tribe of Issachar, according to its families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:18",
      "text": "Its territory included Jezreel, Chesulloth, Shunem,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:19",
      "text": "Haphara-im, Shion, Anaharath,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:20",
      "text": "Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:21",
      "text": "Remeth, En-gannim, En-haddah, Beth-pazzez;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:22",
      "text": "the boundary also touches Tabor, Shahazumah, and Beth-shemesh, and its boundary ends at the Jordan—sixteen cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:23",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of Issachar, according to its families—the cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:24",
      "text": "The fifth lot came out for the tribe of Asher according to its families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:25",
      "text": "Its territory included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:26",
      "text": "Allammelech, Amad, and Mishal; on the west it touches Carmel and Shihor-libnath,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:27",
      "text": "then it turns eastward, it goes to Beth-dagon, and touches Zebulun and the valley of Iphtahel northward to Beth-emek and Neiel; then it continues in the north to Cabul,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:28",
      "text": "Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, Kanah, as far as Sidon the Great;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:29",
      "text": "then the boundary turns to Ramah, reaching to the fortified city of Tyre; then the boundary turns to Hosah, and it ends at the sea; Mahalab, Achzib,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:30",
      "text": "Ummah, Aphek and Rehob—twenty-two cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:31",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of Asher according to its families—these cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:32",
      "text": "The sixth lot came out for the tribe of Naphtali, for the tribe of Naphtali, according to its families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:33",
      "text": "And its boundary ran from Heleph, from the oak in Za-anannim, and Adami-nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum; and it ended at the Jordan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:34",
      "text": "then the boundary turns westward to Aznoth-tabor, and goes from there to Hukkok, touching Zebulun at the south, and Asher on the west, and Judah on the east at the Jordan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:35",
      "text": "The fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Chinnereth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:36",
      "text": "Adamah, Ramah, Hazor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:37",
      "text": "Kedesh, Edre-i, En-hazor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:38",
      "text": "Yiron, Migdal-el, Horem, Beth-anath, and Beth-shemesh—nineteen cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:39",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of Naphtali according to its families—the cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:40",
      "text": "The seventh lot came out for the tribe of Dan, according to its families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:41",
      "text": "And the territory of its inheritance included Zorah, Eshta-ol, Ir-shemesh,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:42",
      "text": "Sha-alabbin, Aijalon, Ithlah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:43",
      "text": "Elon, Timnah, Ekron,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:44",
      "text": "Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:45",
      "text": "Jehud, Bene-berak, Gath-rimmon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:46",
      "text": "and Me-jarkon and Rakkon with the territory over against Joppa.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:47",
      "text": "When the territory of the Danites was lost to them, the Danites went up and fought against Leshem, and after capturing it and putting it to the sword they took possession of it and settled in it, calling Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their ancestor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:48",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of Dan, according to their families—these cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:49",
      "text": "When they had finished distributing the several territories of the land as inheritances, the people of Israel gave an inheritance among them to Joshua the son of Nun.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:50",
      "text": "By command of the Lord they gave him the city which he asked, Timnath-serah in the hill country of Ephraim; and he rebuilt the city, and settled in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.19.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 19:51",
      "text": "These are the inheritances which Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and the heads of the fathers' houses of the tribes of the people of Israel distributed by lot at Shiloh before the Lord, at the door of the tent of meeting. So they finished dividing the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
